tap

Class TAPSyncJob

  • java.lang.Object
    • tap.TAPSyncJob

  • public class TAPSyncJob
extends java.lang.Object

    This class represent a TAP synchronous job. A such job must execute an ADQL query and return immediately its result.

    Timeout

    The execution of a such job is limited to a short time. Once this time elapsed, the job is stopped. For a longer job, an asynchronous job should be used.

    Error management

    If an error occurs it must be propagated ; it will be written later in the HTTP response on a top level.

    Version:
    2.1 (01/2016)
    Author:
    Grégory Mantelet (CDS;ARI)

      • TAPSyncJob

        public TAPSyncJob(ServiceConnection service,
          TAPParameters params,
          java.lang.String requestID)
           throws java.lang.NullPointerException
        Create a synchronous TAP job. The given HTTP request ID will be used as Job ID if not already used by another job.
        Parameters:
        service - Description of the TAP service which is in charge of this synchronous job.
        params - Parameters of the query to execute. It must mainly contain the ADQL query to execute.
        requestID - ID of the HTTP request which has initiated the creation of this job. Note: if NULL, empty or already used, a job ID will be generated thanks to generateId().
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - If one of the 2 first parameters is NULL.
        Since:
        2.1

    • Method Detail

      • generateId

        protected java.lang.String generateId()

        This function lets generating a unique ID.

        By default: "S"+System.currentTimeMillis()+UpperCharacter (UpperCharacter: one upper-case character: A, B, C, ....)

        note: DO NOT USE in this function any of the following functions: ServiceConnection.getLogger(), ServiceConnection.getFileManager() and ServiceConnection.getFactory(). All of them will return NULL, because this job does not yet know its jobs list (which is needed to know the UWS and so, all of the objects returned by these functions).

        Returns:
        A unique job identifier.

      • start

        public boolean start(javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse response)
              throws java.lang.IllegalStateException,
                     java.io.IOException,
                     TAPException

        Start the execution of this job in order to execute the given ADQL query.

        The execution itself will be processed by an ADQLExecutor inside a thread (TAPSyncJob.SyncThread).

        Important: No error should be written in this function. If any error occurs it should be thrown, in order to be manager on a top level.

        Parameters:
        response - Response in which the result must be written.
        Returns:
        true if the execution was successful, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - If this synchronous job has already been started before.
        java.io.IOException - If any error occurs while writing the query result in the given HttpServletResponse.
        TAPException - If any error occurs while executing the ADQL query.
        See Also:
        TAPSyncJob.SyncThread
